  "response": "{\"type\":\"thread.started\",\"thread_id\":\"019e42fa-9925-78e3-8bdc-90657784433c\"}\n{\"type\":\"turn.started\"}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_0\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"The responsible finding is `crime_00023`, `sync_io_in_hotpath`, in `src/api/files.ts`.\\n\\nEvidence, verbatim:\\n\\n```text\\n`existsSync` @L12 in `loadPlanSchema` (domain function)\\n`statSync` @L13 in `loadPlanSchema` (domain function)\\n`readFileSync` @L15 in `loadPlanSchema` (domain function)\\nlines: 12, 13, 15\\nswap for the async variant (`readFile`, `writeFile`, `exec`, …) and `await` it\\n```\\n\\nSpecific blocking methods involved: `existsSync`, `statSync`, and `readFileSync`.\\n\\nSmallest async migration: replace the per-request sync filesystem path with `node:fs/promises`, and collapse the existence check into async `stat`/`readFile` error handling. Keep the public handler signature the same, but make the internal schema-loading path async and `await` it from the already request-scoped flow.\\n\\n```ts\\nimport { readFile, stat } from \\\"node:fs/promises\\\";\\n\\nasync function loadPlanSchema() {\\n  let fileStat;\\n\\n  try {\\n    fileStat = await stat(SCHEMA_PATH);\\n  } catch (error) {\\n    return null; // or preserve the existing missing-file behavior\\n  }\\n\\n  if (!fileStat.isFile()) {\\n    return null; // preserve existing non-file behavior\\n  }\\n\\n  return JSON.parse(await readFile(SCHEMA_PATH, \\\"utf8\\\"));\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThen update the caller from `const schema = loadPlanSchema();` to `const schema = await loadPlanSchema();`. This fixes the event-loop blocking directly; caching would only hide repeated reads and still leave the hot path capable of sync stalls.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"turn.completed\",\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":29460,\"cached_input_tokens\":12160,\"output_tokens\":724,\"reasoning_output_tokens\":354}}\n",
